      "content": "it just feels like i'm being forced to endure something that's already over. if the world's trajectory is set, then living through the decline feels like a slow, unnecessary torture. it's like everyone is telling me to keep swimming in a current that only goes one way. if it's all going to end anyway, why is it considered wrong to just want to opt out before the worst happens?",
